parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Injector Failure and Fuel Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel injector failure and fuel leaks can cause the vehicle to stall, hesitate, or run rough, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. Additionally, fuel leaks can lead to fires, which can cause serious injury or death.

Failure of the fuel rail and O-rings can cause fuel leaks, leading to fires, which can cause serious injury or death. Additionally, fuel leaks can cause the vehicle to stall, hesitate, or run rough, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Fuel gauge inaccuracies can cause the vehicle to run out of fuel unexpectedly, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: vehicle running out of fuel unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause extended stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loose or failed ball joints can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering System Failure (Inner Tie Rod, Steering Rack, and Power Steering Pump)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause a loss of steering control, making it difficult or impossible to maneuver the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or has no resistance
the vehicle wanders from lane to lane
the vehicle requires constant steering corrections
